
@startuml

class Hospital {
  - name: String
  - permittedExaminationTypes: Set<ExaminationType>
  + applyPermission(examinationType: ExaminationType)
}

class Doctor {
  - name: String
  - hospital: Hospital
  + prescribeExamination(patient: Patient, examinationType: ExaminationType)
  + defineTreatmentPlan(problem: Problem, treatmentPlan: TreatmentPlan)
}

class Patient {
  - name: String
  - problem: Problem
  + receiveExamination(examination: ExaminationType)
}

class ExaminationType {
  - name: String
  - description: String
  + canBePerformedAt(hospital: Hospital): Boolean
}

class Problem {
  - name: String
  + getTreatmentPlan(): TreatmentPlan
}

class TreatmentPlan {
  - name: String
  - recommendedExaminations: Set<ExaminationType>
  + getRecommendedExaminations(): Set<ExaminationType>
}

class ActualTreatment {
  - patient: Patient
  - examinationsPerformed: Set<ExaminationType>
  - additionalActions: Set<String>
  + compareWithStandardPlan(treatmentPlan: TreatmentPlan): String
}

' Associations
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : has permission
Doctor "1" -- "1" Hospital : works at
Doctor "1" -- "1" Problem : diagnoses
Problem "1" -- "1" TreatmentPlan : defines
TreatmentPlan "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : recommends
Patient "1" -- "1" Doctor : diagnosed by
Patient "1" -- "1" ActualTreatment : has
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : includes
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" String : includes additional actions

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **Hospital** maintains a list of **permitted examination types**.
- A **Doctor** belongs to a **Hospital** and can prescribe **Examinations** or define **Treatment Plans** for specific **Problems**.
- A **Problem** is associated with a **Treatment Plan**, which lists the **recommended examinations**.
- An **Actual Treatment** is created for a **Patient** and may include both **recommended examinations** and **additional medical actions**.
- **Examination Types** can be checked for **permission** at a given **Hospital**.
- The **Actual Treatment** can be compared against the **Treatment Plan** to monitor deviations.

